  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Application Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role & Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Support sales activities through product demonstrations, application consultations, and technical presentations.</li><li>Assist with equipment installation, system setup, and configuration at customer sites.</li><li>Provide technical support for device integration, including hardware‑software connectivity and system configuration.</li><li>Perform interoperability and system validation testing to ensure compatibility and performance across device.</li><li>Troubleshoot application‑related issues and deliver effective after‑sales support.</li><li>Participate in product launches, workshops, seminars, and exhibitions.</li><li>Conduct user training on hardware and software applications.</li><li>Prepare and handle biological samples for demonstrations, testing, and training.</li><li>Support product evaluations, field trials, and new application development.</li><li>Support customers across Singapore and ASEAN countries.</li><li>Act as a technical liaison between customers, sales teams, service engineers, and regional product teams.</li><li>Gather customer feedback to support product and application improvements.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in biomedical engineering, Life Sciences, Biotechnology, Optics, Electronics Engineering, or a related field.</li><li>At least 5 years of experience in microscopy, application engineering, and optoelectronic device integration and interoperability testing, system configuration.</li><li>Hands-on experience in microscopy installation, calibration or troubleshooting.</li><li>Able to explain technical concepts clearly to customers and non‑technical users.</li><li>Strong communication and presentation skills.</li><li>Customer‑focused, proactive, and solution‑driven.</li><li>Willingness to travel occasionally for overseas assignments.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
